               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; names of the owners; name of the King Ḫaylä Śǝllase in the colophon.&#xD;
A group of lines, alternating with black lines, in the incipit page of Texts I, II, and in the incipit of Text III; incipit (2 lines) of each sub section (homilies) in Text I and of each miracle in Text II; the word sälam in Text  III; initial line of the colophon.&#xD;
Elements of Ethiopian numerals, of punctuations signs and of text dividers; marginal notes or their decorative elements; elements of quire marks.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus>&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="line-height</locus><p><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt">Fol. 89ra: </span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala; font-size: 14pt">&#4720;&#4936;&#4920;&#4632;&#4961; &#4829;&#4757;&#4721;&#4961; &#4632;&#4925;&#4624;&#4941;&#4961; &#4768;&#4632;&#4961; &#4970;&#4616;&#4915;&#4873;&#4636;&#4757;&#4961; &#4704;&#4978;&#4808;&#4977;&#4987;&#4983;&#4808;&#4970;&#4819;&#4632;&#4720;&#4961; &#4637;&#4629;&#4648;&#4725;&#4961; &#4704;&#4980;&#4808;&#4977;&#4824;&#4632;&#4752;&#4961; &#4632;&#4757;&#4877;&#4645;&#4721;&#4961; &#4616;&#4757;&#4873;&#4645;&#4752;&#4961; &#4739;&#4845;&#4616;&#4961; &#4645;&#4619;&#4660;&#4961; &#4704;&#4773;&#4848;&#4961; &#4920;&#4624;&#4938;&#4609;&#4961; &#4768;&#4616;&#4675;&#4961; &#4853;&#4651;&#4653;&#4961; &#4808;</span><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala; font-size: 14pt"><span lang="AMH" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala; font-size: 14pt">&#4621;</span>&#4848;&#4961; &#4674;&#4653;&#4678;&#4661;&#4961; &#4824;&#4709;&#4628;&#4648;&#4961; &#4621;&#4875;&#4725;&#4961; &#4808;&#4824;&#4768;&#4925;&#4624;&#4936;&#4726;&#4961; &#4808;&#4845;&#4824;&#4654;&#4961; &#4637;&#4629;&#4648;&#4723;&#4961; &#4808;&#4621;&#4848;&#4961; &#4778;&#4851;&#4757;&#4961; &#4704;&#4987;&#4808;&#4979;&#4709;&#4649;&#4653;&#4961; &#4808;&#4808;&#4608;&#4704;&#4726;&#4961; &#4616;&#4723;&#4710;&#4720;&#4961; &#4846;&#4624;&#4757;&#4656;&#4961; &#4848;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4635;&#4821;&#4926;&#4968; &#4824;&#4640;&#4648;&#4678;&#4961; &#4808;&#4824;&#4936;&#4624;&#4678;&#4961; &#4653;&#4873;&#4632;&#4961; &#4845;&#4777;&#4757;&#4961; &#4776;&#4632;&#4961; &#4768;&#4653;&#4846;&#4661;&#4961; &#4704;&#4645;&#4621;&#4899;&#4752;&#4961; &#4916;&#4901;&#4654;&#4661;&#4961; &#4808;&#4915;&#4813;&#4622;&#4661;&#4961; &#4616;&#4845;&#4777;&#4757;&#4961; &#4616;&#4845;&#4777;&#4757;&#4961; &#4616;&#4845;&#4777;&#4757;&#4968;</span></p><foreign xml:lang="en"><p><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt">Fol. 89ra:</span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Nyala; font-size: 10pt"> </span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt">This book was completed on the 2nd &#7766;agumen, in the year of mercy 1962, in 39<sup>th</sup> year of the reign of our King &#7722;ayl&#228; &#346;&#1241;llase, by the hands of his scribe &#704;al&#228;qa D&#601;rar W&#228;ld&#228; Qirqos, of the region of L&#1241;gat. And the one who let him write (was) w&#228;yz&#228;ro M&#1241;&#7717;r&#228;ta W&#228;ld&#228; Kidan, for 120 B&#1241;rur, and she gave it to the tabot of Yo&#7717;ann&#1241;s of <span>D&#228;br&#228; Ma&#705;&#7779;o. Anyone who stole it, or who erased it, be cursed like Arius by authority of Peter and Paul. So be it, so be it, so be it.</span></span></p></foreign>
                        <note>2nd Ṗagumen, 1962 of the year of mercy (= 6 September 1969 A.D.) is indicated as the date of the completion of the manuscript. Lǝgat is the place and church (of Qirqos) located close to Zälambäsa.</note>
                     </colophon>
